# Pull request descriptions

When the user asks for a PR description, opening PR text, or merge-request summary, **fill and output this template** (replace placeholders like `{TICKET_ID}` with real values; omit sections only if truly N/A).

````markdown
# PR Description — {TICKET_ID}

---

## Summary

{One paragraph: what this PR does, why, and the user-facing behavior change. Reference the ticket ID. Mention key implementation approach (e.g., "CSS-only", "no new dependencies"). Call out what is NOT changed if relevant.}

---

## What Changed

- **{Area 1}**: {Concise description of changes in this area. Include specific values, class names, props, config — be precise enough that a reviewer knows what to look for.}
- **{Area 2}**: {Same format. Group by logical area: Frontend, Backend, Tests, Config, Infra, etc.}
- **Tests**: {What tests were added/updated. Note any testing limitations (e.g., "not asserted in JSDOM due to mocked CSS").}

---

## Files Modified

| Area     | File                          | Change                                                    |
| -------- | ----------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------- |
| {Area}   | `{path/to/file}`             | {Brief description of what changed in this file}          |
| {Area}   | `{path/to/file}`             | {Brief description}                                       |

---

## Alternative: Plain-text version (if Markdown tables aren't supported)

<!-- Include this section when the target platform (e.g., some CI tools, email) doesn't render Markdown tables. Otherwise, the Markdown version above is sufficient. -->

```text
Summary
{Same summary as above, but with quotes instead of backticks for inline code.}

What Changed
- {Area}: {description}
- Tests: {description}

Files Modified
- {path/to/file} — {description}
- {path/to/file} — {description}
```

---
````

Do not substitute a shorter format unless the user explicitly asks for something different.
